<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-23T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="221" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d221">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Conference/294: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-24T00:00:00+00:00">November 24,
                                        1937—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received November 24—11:40
                                    p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>52. 1. The Conference recessed this evening after adopting with only
                                Italy abstaining, a single report, the full text of which follows in
                                the next telegram.<note n="9" xml:id="d221fn9">For text of report,
                                    see <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_417"><hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 417</ref>.</note> This will
                                be sent to all governments for their authentic information.</p>
                            <p>2. I am planning to leave for Paris tomorrow evening and shall
                                probably remain there or in the vicinity until the sailing of the
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>, December 2.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>